// ************ device file format ********************

// DEVICEDEF   // DEVICEDEF begins the device definition

//    //  1. comments and blank lines are permitted anywhere
//    //  2. any line not beginning with a double "slash" is part
//    //     of the device definition.

//   device_name      // name or label for device
//   .var1 ... .varn  // a series of variables may be specified for use by
//                    // the device definition.  Smokeview copies data into
//                    // these variables from the SMOKEVIEW_PARAMETERS
//                    // keyword in the FDS input file.  The data in .varn
//                    // is referenced  elsewhere in the definition
//                    // using $varn

//   // A series of argument/command pairs are specified on one or
//   // more lines.

//   arg1 ... argn command1 arg1 ... argn command2 ...

//   // An argument may be a numerical constant (e.g. 2.37),
//   // a label (e.g. .var1) or a reference to a label located
//   // elsewhere (e.g. $var1)

// NEWFRAME    // beginning of next frame
//  more argument/command pairs for next device frame
//  ....

   // ************ static device definitions - single frame/state ********************

